name: Daniel Craig
summary: Daniel Craig's portrayal of James Bond has had a significant impact on his personal life. His family found it emotionally challenging to witness his transformation into the iconic secret agent. The role also affected his emotional well-being, leaving him "empty and exhausted," and requiring months to recover from filming. Craig acknowledges that playing the role of Bond would have hindered his ability to take on the role in the gay romance film "Queer," as it could have been perceived as a reactionary move. Balancing his busy career with his family has been a challenge, but he has learned to navigate the difficulties of fame. Despite the personal tolls, Craig has found joy in playing Bond, embracing the fashion transformations and the cultural impact of the role.
